China to Raise Rare Earth Minerals Resource Tax, Herald Reports

-- B y   B l o o m b e r g   N e w s
-- 
2011-03-24T06:09:01Z

-- http://www.bloomberg.com/news/2011-03-24/china-to-raise-rare-earth-minerals-resource-tax-herald-reports.html
China  will raise resource taxes on
rare earth minerals from April 1, the 21st Century Business
Herald  reported , citing a government document.  The tax will rise to 60 yuan per ton of mined light rare
earths, while medium and heavy rare earths will be taxed at 30
yuan a ton, the report said, citing the Ministry of Finance. It
didnâ€™t say what the previous tax levels were.  --Xiao Yu. Editor: Alan Soughley,  To contact Bloomberg News staff on this story:
